SESComponents
-------------

Shared component package used by Strathclyde Electrophysiology Software application programs.

The component package SESCOMPONENT must be installed on the Delphi V7 IDE toolbar before building/editing applications.

To install the package:

1) Import the SESComponents repository into the folder <your Delphi projects folder>\Components"
2) Select File/Open Project
3) Select Files of Type "*.dpk"
4) Select the "Components" Folder
5) Select "SESCOMPONENT"
6) Click the Install button
7) Select Tools/Environment Options
8) Select the "Library" panel
9) Click "..." at the right of Library Path
10) Add "$<your Delphi projects folder>\SESComponents" to the library 

Note. SESCOMPONENTS includes a copy of the GraphicEX library produced by  Mike Lischke (http://www.lischke-online.de/index.php/libs/graphicex-library)
